- You can have the below software installed on your laptops 

For Day1:

Please create a directory under c or d drive and name it as DevOps
Let us have all action done on the same DevOps directory 
You need to be flexible with commandline as well through GUI
Should know  basic commands like how to Change directory (CD), create files,directories etc

JIRA-->https://www.atlassian.com/software/jira/download
git --> https://git-scm.com/downloads
MAVEN-->https://maven.apache.org/download.cgi?Preferred=ftp://mirror.reverse.net/pub/apache/
Download maven and extract to a directory on local machines
JDK1.8-->http://www.oracle.com/technetwork/java/javase/downloads/jdk8-downloads-2133151.html
Make sure that JAVA_HOME environment variable is created and is pointing towards JDK instalaltion folder
Eg: (C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.8.0_45)

Make sure that MVN_HOME variable is set as the extracted maven folder path
Eg: C:\SW\apache-maven-3.3.9)

Make sure that following paths are added to the System Path

- JDK Bin Folder (Eg:C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.8.0_45\bin)
- Apache Maven Bin folder (Eg:C:\SW\apache-maven-3.3.9\bin)
- git bin folder (Eg:c:\programfiles\git\bin )
- git user/bin foldeer (C:\Local\Programs\Git\usr\bin)

go to command prompt and make sure that all the below commands are getting executed

1)git
2)mvn
3)javac

Make sure all have a github free account created and also please create a simple github repository

For Day 2:

Nexus:http://www.sonatype.com/download-oss-sonatype
jenkins: https://jenkins.io/ (Please make a note of password which you will be seeing in a log file during installation,also remmber the username)

For Day 3:

oracle virtual box ---> https://www.virtualbox.org/

vagrant-->https://www.vagrantup.com/downloads.html
sublime ---> https://www.sublimetext.com/3
chefdk-->https://downloads.chef.io/chef-dk/mac/
putty =>http://www.putty.org/
Browsers --> firefox & chrome
winzip or winrar

Execute: vagrant plugin install vagrant-hostmanager

Docker: https://www.docker.com/ (Preferably on a linux machine)


*****Please Note: Run the below commands once you have vagrant installed (Note : Needs high speed intenet)
mkdir c:\DevOps
cd c:\DevOps
vagrant init hashicorp/precise64
vagrant up

